column5: http://www.nugget.ca/2016/01/21/police-investigate-suspicious-object    Ice fishermen contacted Ontario Provincial Police earlier this week after their fishfinder picked up images of a “suspicious object” on the bottom of a lake. OPP Const Carolyn Ward said officers attended the scene at Champlain Park on the shores of Lake Nipissing to investigate the discovery.  “The fishermen thought what they saw was unusual, so they contacted police, but it turned out to be clam shells,” she said Thursday afternoon.
Years ago in the Minden Times, "cottager sees UFO at 2am while in his hot tub, he was admittedly drinking at the time"  Gotta love the small town news.
Slow news day in the bay
I would pay good money to witness this event from start to finish.
